The evidence with the title 'No cost-of-living adjustment for 2016 | social security matters ' says Oct 15, 2015  ... By law , the monthly Social Security and ssi federal benefit rate increases when there is a rise in the cost of living . The government measures changes in the cost of living through the Department Of Labor 's Consumer Price Index (CPI-w). The CPI has not risen since the last cost - of - living adjustmentin2015.
